00:40:50,730 --> 00:40:52,640
just what in the hell is going on here!

575
00:41:21,030 --> 00:41:22,070
Come with me.

576
00:41:33,310 --> 00:41:35,490
I'm not sure what I am supposed to say

577
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:37,720
if what I've just heard is true.

578
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:40,740
Rajan, I know it's not an easy thing, okay?

579
00:41:40,740 --> 00:41:43,580
It took me a long time myself to accept that--

580
00:41:43,630 --> 00:41:49,380
That you are... A different type of human being to me.

581
00:41:49,770 --> 00:41:50,610
Yes.

582
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:54,680
That you are telepathically connected to seven other people.

583
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:56,880
Telepathy's not exactly...

584
00:41:58,670 --> 00:42:00,320
But basically, yes.

585
00:42:04,260 --> 00:42:07,780
And here I thought I was the one with the big secrets.

586
00:42:08,470 --> 00:42:10,110
I didn't know how to tell you.

587
00:42:11,170 --> 00:42:12,320
Or anyone.

588
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:17,870
And this was all happening to you before our wedding?

589
00:42:19,190 --> 00:42:20,090
Yes.

590
00:42:21,830 --> 00:42:24,170
Little wonder you were so confused.

591
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:26,680
Yes.

592
00:42:27,970 --> 00:42:31,040
And in... Positano?

593
00:42:32,570 --> 00:42:33,520
Yes!

594
00:42:36,670 --> 00:42:41,010
So, when this Wolfgang fellow is tortured,

595
00:42:41,010 --> 00:42:43,400
you experience his pain?

596
00:42:46,990 --> 00:42:48,410
That sounds terrible.

597
00:42:54,790 --> 00:42:55,680
Look...

598
00:42:56,430 --> 00:42:58,240
I know this is all a shock

599
00:42:58,240 --> 00:43:00,830
and that it might be best for you

600
00:43:00,830 --> 00:43:03,130
to take some time away and just--

601
00:43:03,130 --> 00:43:04,850
But you are in danger now, Kala.

602
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:08,460
So you believe me?

603
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:13,870
Would you, could you concoct a lie of this extraordinary magnitude?

604
00:43:14,730 --> 00:43:15,600
No.

605
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:20,410
Are you and all of these people out there medically insane?

606
00:43:20,930 --> 00:43:22,110
I don't think so.

607
00:43:22,110 --> 00:43:23,740
So what other choice do I have?

608
00:43:28,150 --> 00:43:31,750
I came rushing to Paris for the same reason I married you.

609
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:33,490
I love you, Kala.

610
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:37,640
And that feeling hasn't gone away or been changed

611
00:43:37,910 --> 00:43:40,330
by learning that the woman I love...

612
00:43:42,260 --> 00:43:44,410
is so much more than the woman I married.

613
00:43:45,470 --> 00:43:49,130
My God, Rajan.

614
00:43:51,700 --> 00:43:53,400
I married a good man.

616
00:44:13,610 --> 00:44:15,770
Sans Jour is down there, next to the river.

617
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:18,080
It's close to the metro. That's good for us.

618
00:44:18,270 --> 00:44:20,320
Georges said there's a back entrance we could use

619
00:44:20,320 --> 00:44:22,410
and they could bring in extra security.

620
00:44:22,420 --> 00:44:24,660
These club owners are really into you, aren't they?

621
00:44:31,170 --> 00:44:33,530
Oh, how I've missed you.

622
00:44:36,100 --> 00:44:37,880
As beautiful as ever.

623
00:44:45,280 --> 00:44:46,530
This is Will,

624
00:44:46,670 --> 00:44:48,390
the one I told you about.

625
00:44:49,850 --> 00:44:52,670
My rival. Very well.

626
00:44:53,040 --> 00:44:54,500
Shall we say pistols at dawn?

627
00:44:56,210 --> 00:44:58,190
English only, I imagine.

628
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:00,680
French if you prefer.

629
00:45:00,680 --> 00:45:04,440
And pistols suit me just fucking fine.

630
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:07,040
I like him already.

631
00:45:07,490 --> 00:45:08,440
Come.

632
00:45:11,530 --> 00:45:14,560
- You know French? - No, but you do.

633
00:45:17,050 --> 00:45:20,570
I have a certain understanding with the local police.

634
00:45:21,370 --> 00:45:24,090
It's not the local police we're worried about.

635
00:45:24,920 --> 00:45:29,890
Vincent told me these men threatened to close his club down.

636
00:45:32,770 --> 00:45:36,650
We've had many kinds of people threaten us in Paris...

637
00:45:37,360 --> 00:45:39,910
attack us and our way of life.

638
00:45:43,340 --> 00:45:45,810
Our answer has been and will always be the same.

639
00:45:48,450 --> 00:45:49,920
Vive la résistance.

640
00:45:51,870 --> 00:45:55,740
Or like you say in English, "Fuck off."

641
00:45:58,150 --> 00:45:59,250
Give me that.

642
00:45:59,430 --> 00:46:01,000
If Will is right and

643
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:03,980
Angelica and Whispers came to London together...

644
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:06,580
whatever happened there could explain the rift

645
00:46:06,580 --> 00:46:08,900
that shunted Kolovi out of the picture.

646
00:46:08,900 --> 00:46:09,810
Right.

647
00:46:14,460 --> 00:46:15,460
Blocker time.

648
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:18,250
Right. Just a moment, let me get the shot ready.

649
00:46:22,140 --> 00:46:23,080
You were right.

650
00:46:23,580 --> 00:46:25,020
Georges is one of a kind.

651
00:46:25,940 --> 00:46:27,520
So how close were you two?

652
00:46:28,300 --> 00:46:30,330
You know... close.

653
00:46:35,800 --> 00:46:38,520
Okay, my bad cop feeling about this is buzzing.

654
00:46:38,700 --> 00:46:39,570
What?

655
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:41,310
Someone's following us.

656
00:47:34,290 --> 00:47:35,220
Shit.

657
00:47:36,150 --> 00:47:37,910
- Do you have your phone? - No.

658
00:47:37,910 --> 00:47:38,830
Let's go.

659
00:47:39,340 --> 00:47:40,290
Ringing.

660
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:41,770
It just keeps ringing.

661
00:47:42,640 --> 00:47:43,560
Nothing.

662
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:45,920
You can't visit?

663
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:47,940
They're on blockers.

664
00:47:50,290 --> 00:47:51,380
What about Capheus?

665
00:48:04,780 --> 00:48:05,680
What's up?

666
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,270
We have a problem.

667
00:48:12,260 --> 00:48:13,400
You're nowhere near the squat.

668
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:15,490
- I could drive. - You'll be too late.

669
00:48:15,490 --> 00:48:18,080
Whispers will be off the blockers if he isn't already.

670
00:48:18,190 --> 00:48:20,980
This is not like Will. Something's wrong.

671
00:48:20,980 --> 00:48:21,890
Very wrong.

672
00:48:21,890 --> 00:48:23,280
In 10 minutes, Whispers will be able

673
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:24,870
to visit with anyone he's connected to.

674
00:48:24,870 --> 00:48:26,870
If he knows about where we are...

675
00:48:27,030 --> 00:48:27,970
I'll go.

676
00:48:28,970 --> 00:48:29,810
What?

677
00:48:30,570 --> 00:48:32,590
No. No way.

678
00:48:32,590 --> 00:48:34,500
We talked about it. He already knows me.

679
00:48:34,500 --> 00:48:35,670
I can do the shot.

680
00:48:36,540 --> 00:48:38,390
I just need someone to watch my back.

681
00:48:41,780 --> 00:48:43,510
Anyone know how to use this thing?

682
00:49:02,800 --> 00:49:03,720
Joaquin.

683
00:49:04,610 --> 00:49:06,390
My tía always said that

684
00:49:06,400 --> 00:49:09,130
even assholes are useful for shitting and fucking.

685
00:49:15,610 --> 00:49:17,500
Oh, Ms. Caplan.

686
00:49:17,820 --> 00:49:19,880
Come to play doctors and nurses?

687
00:49:20,300 --> 00:49:22,620
Is it easy for you to sound like a creepy villain

688
00:49:22,620 --> 00:49:24,320
or is it something you have to work at?

689
00:49:24,330 --> 00:49:27,010
On the stool. Eyes to the wall. You know the routine.

690
00:49:32,650 --> 00:49:35,440
And who's the sidekick's sidekick?

691
00:49:36,870 --> 00:49:40,100
Too afraid to show your Latina face?

692
00:49:41,970 --> 00:49:43,770
Aren't there more convivial ways

693
00:49:43,770 --> 00:49:48,540
for two pretty ladies to occupy their time in gay Paris?

694
00:49:49,340 --> 00:49:51,070
Oh, you don't have to say anything.

695
00:49:51,210 --> 00:49:54,010
Your desire for shopping is palpable.

696
00:49:56,140 --> 00:49:57,850
Oh, did that hurt?

697
00:50:03,500 --> 00:50:05,890
An engagement ring, Ms. Caplan?

698
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:07,980
Given your recent failed marriage,

699
00:50:07,980 --> 00:50:11,010
I'll pass on whatever sage wisdom you were considering sharing.

700
00:50:11,130 --> 00:50:12,070
Yes.

701
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:14,820
Well in due time, you too will discover

702
00:50:14,830 --> 00:50:17,440
the unbridgeable differences between our species.

703
00:50:17,510 --> 00:50:22,660
It's the smallness of your kind, the limits of the sapien mind

704
00:50:22,670 --> 00:50:25,010
that attracts my kind.

705
00:50:25,900 --> 00:50:29,860
It's akin to the way humans like to keep their pets.

706
00:50:30,880 --> 00:50:32,620
Sooner rather than later,

707
00:50:32,710 --> 00:50:35,100
Ms. Marks will discover that being married to you

708
00:50:35,100 --> 00:50:38,570
is no different from being married to a Labrador bitch.

709
00:50:48,630 --> 00:50:50,460
I never forget a face.

710
00:50:50,860 --> 00:50:52,220
I see you too.

711
00:50:57,320 --> 00:50:58,250
Tricky.

712
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,170
And I know your kind.

713
00:51:04,950 --> 00:51:07,710
Men that mistake cruelty for strength.

714
00:51:08,670 --> 00:51:11,730
Living your petty little lives, so limited.

715
00:51:11,730 --> 00:51:14,510
We both know that if I were to pull this trigger,

716
00:51:14,520 --> 00:51:17,230
not a single person would shed a tear.

717
00:51:17,990 --> 00:51:22,350
The smallness of your kind of life is nothing to fear...

718
00:51:23,450 --> 00:51:24,870
only to pity.

719
00:51:36,890 --> 00:51:38,160
Okay, that rocked!

720
00:51:41,840 --> 00:51:42,770
It was Bodhi.

721
00:51:42,960 --> 00:51:43,970
From the plane?

722
00:51:44,290 --> 00:51:46,980
I thought she said it was pointless to try to change the world.

723
00:51:46,980 --> 00:51:48,790
That you can only change yourself.

724
00:51:49,170 --> 00:51:50,910
Apparently her rules have changed.

725
00:51:51,340 --> 00:51:54,620
She's not the only one changing the way the game is played.

726
00:51:54,990 --> 00:51:55,970
Mr. Hoy!

727
00:51:59,440 --> 00:52:01,500
- What's happening? - A purge!

728
00:52:01,600 --> 00:52:05,170
As you can see, the trap snaps shut.

729
00:52:14,270 --> 00:52:17,250
Come on now, Ms. Blue, before they hang, draw, and quarter me.

730
00:52:17,250 --> 00:52:20,050
I've got two ladies who want words.

731
00:52:21,190 --> 00:52:25,180
You may recall your fellow countrywoman.

732
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:28,330
Yrsa?

733
00:52:29,660 --> 00:52:31,040
You're still alive!

734
00:52:31,470 --> 00:52:32,860
I am, Riley.

735
00:52:33,710 --> 00:52:34,750
For now.

736
00:52:35,010 --> 00:52:36,710
Kala, what's happening?

737
00:52:37,070 --> 00:52:39,070
Riley's visiting Mr. Hoy.

738
00:52:39,800 --> 00:52:41,080
But she's here.

739
00:52:41,930 --> 00:52:42,900
Been there.

740
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:46,670
I've been in hiding since I fled Iceland.

741
00:52:47,310 --> 00:52:50,840
BPO knows that I feigned a heart attack to bring the ambulance.

742
00:52:51,190 --> 00:52:52,100
It was you.

743
00:52:53,100 --> 00:52:54,390
You saved my life.

744
00:52:54,390 --> 00:52:56,020
If you want to thank me,

745
00:52:56,270 --> 00:52:58,890
listen to the woman who urged me to help you.

746
00:53:00,180 --> 00:53:03,800
Riley, I'm a sapien, so I can't see you.

747
00:53:04,940 --> 00:53:08,410
My name is River El-Saadawi. You may have heard of my mother.

748
00:53:08,970 --> 00:53:10,170
Of course.

749
00:53:10,190 --> 00:53:12,550
I lead the faction inside BPO

750
00:53:12,550 --> 00:53:15,450
still fighting to return to the original principles

751
00:53:15,450 --> 00:53:18,150
as envisioned by my mother and Mr. Hoy.

752
00:53:20,290 --> 00:53:24,220
Those days are long gone, and I'm afeard I'm right behind them.

753
00:53:28,860 --> 00:53:29,650
Hoy.

754
00:53:29,650 --> 00:53:32,010
They're attacking our people in Manchuria.

755
00:53:32,010 --> 00:53:34,660
Evacuate whoever's left to Jeju Island.

756
00:53:35,130 --> 00:53:36,980
Godspeed, Admiral.

757
00:53:36,980 --> 00:53:38,560
You too, Speaker.

758
00:53:39,940 --> 00:53:42,700
Mr. Hoy, the Queen of Naples is behind this purge.

759
00:53:42,700 --> 00:53:45,700
The mendacious minx will be coming for you next, Sutra.

760
00:53:46,220 --> 00:53:47,330
Let us help you.

761
00:53:47,470 --> 00:53:50,570
Oh, you can help me, Ms. Blue,

762
00:53:50,580 --> 00:53:54,270
by keeping your word and paying your debt to the Archipelago.

763
00:53:54,270 --> 00:53:58,290
- How? - By doing what River asks you to do!

764
00:54:00,790 --> 00:54:04,180
I was hoping to have this conversation in person.

765
00:54:04,840 --> 00:54:07,320
I didn't think the situation could get any more dire

766
00:54:07,320 --> 00:54:09,840
after Richard Croome's assassination,

767
00:54:10,150 --> 00:54:13,460
but I obviously underestimated our chairman's ruthlessness.

768
00:54:13,460 --> 00:54:18,560
Like you, we are now being hunted, and imprisoned or worse.

769
00:54:20,730 --> 00:54:23,110
Our only hope is if...

770
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:25,320
If what?

771
00:54:26,500 --> 00:54:28,050
You must kill Whispers.

772
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:33,050
By killing him, you kill the drone program

773
00:54:33,230 --> 00:54:35,980
and cripple the Chairman's hold over the BPO.

774
00:54:37,110 --> 00:54:38,930
I know what it will cost you,

775
00:54:39,360 --> 00:54:40,950
but this is war.

776
00:54:43,010 --> 00:54:44,460
What? What's going on?

777
00:54:44,460 --> 00:54:46,380
It's some kind of organized attack.

778
00:54:46,770 --> 00:54:48,450
BPO has found Hoy.

779
00:54:50,190 --> 00:54:53,240
Ms. El-Saadawi believes that their only hope...

780
00:54:54,270 --> 00:54:55,980
is if we kill Whispers.

781
00:54:56,910 --> 00:55:00,000
But then they will kill Wolfgang.

782
00:55:13,970 --> 00:55:15,000
I'm sorry.

783
00:55:17,390 --> 00:55:18,580
We had to try.

784
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:22,150
Take your blocker, dear.

785
00:55:22,150 --> 00:55:23,760
Exposure is dangerous.

786
00:55:26,690 --> 00:55:29,630
Riley, I pray that one day

787
00:55:29,630 --> 00:55:32,250
we'll somehow emerge from this darkness.

788
00:55:35,470 --> 00:55:36,370
Thank you.

789
00:55:37,930 --> 00:55:38,890
This is it.

790
00:55:40,280 --> 00:55:41,700
This is the end.

791
00:55:45,600 --> 00:55:47,100
Goodbye, Mr. Hoy.

792
00:55:48,250 --> 00:55:49,150
Goodbye.

793
00:55:57,350 --> 00:55:58,480
Where are you going?

794
00:56:12,650 --> 00:56:15,420
I've-- I've nowhere left to run.

795
00:56:19,340 --> 00:56:21,260
You may wish to look away.

796
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:22,980
Don't give up. Please.

797
00:56:23,160 --> 00:56:27,750
Bless you, lassie, but I'm the Speaker of the Archipelago.

798
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:29,990
I can't let BPO get hold of me.

799
00:56:29,990 --> 00:56:32,500
Don't say that. I got you into this.

800
00:56:32,500 --> 00:56:34,430
If we hadn't met in Amsterdam, you'd still be--

801
00:56:34,430 --> 00:56:38,560
Cowering in my coffin, living like a hunted rat?

802
00:56:38,560 --> 00:56:40,350
Aye. I would, Ms. Blue.

803
00:56:40,860 --> 00:56:45,510
But if I died there, I'd die soused in regret.

804
00:56:46,100 --> 00:56:47,020
If I die here--

805
00:56:47,020 --> 00:56:48,600
That's it.

806
00:56:48,910 --> 00:56:52,680
Let's nip in the bud all this nonsense about dying.

807
00:56:52,680 --> 00:56:54,540
- Aunt Kirsty? - Mrs. Stromness?

808
00:56:54,540 --> 00:56:55,770
How did you get here?

809
00:56:55,770 --> 00:56:57,900
By taxi, you great numpty.

810
00:56:57,900 --> 00:57:01,110
What? But... you shouldn't be here!

811
00:57:01,150 --> 00:57:02,090
It's not safe.

812
00:57:02,090 --> 00:57:03,400
Well, it's a great deal safer now

813
00:57:03,400 --> 00:57:05,890
since I chucked the bullets out the window.

814
00:57:07,140 --> 00:57:09,090
What have you done?

815
00:57:10,080 --> 00:57:11,030
Look...

816
00:57:11,380 --> 00:57:14,330
I promised Angus I'd mind you.

817
00:57:14,690 --> 00:57:16,410
So take a blocker.

818
00:57:16,410 --> 00:57:21,270
If we're arrested, it will buy you a period of grace.

819
00:57:22,120 --> 00:57:24,670
You-- You knew?

820
00:57:25,410 --> 00:57:28,530
About Homo sensorium?

821
00:57:28,760 --> 00:57:32,280
I was Angus' wife for 40 years.

822
00:57:32,900 --> 00:57:36,620
You can't love someone like I loved Angus

823
00:57:37,020 --> 00:57:40,050
and not know a thing like that.

824
00:57:40,310 --> 00:57:41,590
Take your medicine.

825
00:57:41,590 --> 00:57:45,030
Don't worry about me. I'll be fine.

826
00:57:45,860 --> 00:57:47,940
- Go! Go! - Clear!

827
00:57:48,060 --> 00:57:49,010
Freeze!

828
00:57:49,840 --> 00:57:52,050
- What happened? - Did Hoy survive?

829
00:57:52,150 --> 00:57:53,210
I don't know.

830
00:57:55,210 --> 00:57:56,720
The connection was broken.

831
00:57:58,110 --> 00:57:59,210
Now he's gone.

832
00:58:14,010 --> 00:58:16,150
You're supposed to say trick or treat.

833
00:58:16,300 --> 00:58:21,110
Cluster zero eight zero eight. Code FH.

834
00:58:21,110 --> 00:58:24,170
F for feral, H for hostile.

835
00:58:24,170 --> 00:58:26,490
And CH is for Chairman.

836
00:58:26,770 --> 00:58:28,800
And also chickenshit.

837
00:58:29,130 --> 00:58:33,210
I'm no more afraid of you than a doctor fears illness.

838
00:58:33,210 --> 00:58:34,680
Then take off your mask.

839
00:58:34,810 --> 00:58:38,760
Anonymity is a regrettable necessity of this war.

840
00:58:38,760 --> 00:58:41,370
But when at last it is over,

841
00:58:41,370 --> 00:58:45,530
I imagine my efforts may well remain uncredited,

842
00:58:45,530 --> 00:58:47,670
which is as it should be.

843
00:58:47,670 --> 00:58:50,190
My work is its own reward.

844
00:58:50,650 --> 00:58:51,660
Don't worry.

